## Summary

`async_openai::types::responses::InputImageContent.detail` is `ImageDetail` with no `#[serde(default)]`. The doc-comment states *"Defaults to `auto`"*, but in practice any spec-compliant payload that omits the field fails to deserialize. Because `InputItem` is `#[serde(untagged)]`, the resulting `missing field 'detail'` error rolls up to the unhelpful `data did not match any variant of untagged enum InputItem`.

Affects v0.38.1 and current `main` (`async-openai/src/types/responses/response.rs:704-715`).

## Repro

```rust
use async_openai::types::responses::InputItem;
use serde_json::json;

fn main() {
    let payload = json!({
        "role": "user",
        "content": [
            {"type": "input_text", "text": "describe this"},
            {"type": "input_image", "image_url": "https://example.com/cat.png"}
        ]
    });
    let result: Result<InputItem, _> = serde_json::from_value(payload);
    println!("{:?}", result);
}
```

**Actual (v0.38.1):**
```
Err(Error("data did not match any variant of untagged enum InputItem", line: 0, column: 0))
```

**Expected:** `Ok(InputItem::EasyMessage(...))` with the `input_image` part's `detail` defaulted to `ImageDetail::Auto`.

## Why this matters

The OpenAI Responses API spec and every official SDK treat `detail` as optional with default `auto`:

- **openai-python** — [`ResponseInputImageParam`](https://github.com/openai/openai-python/blob/main/src/openai/types/responses/response_input_image_param.py): `detail: Optional[Literal[\"low\", \"high\", \"auto\"]]`
- **openai-node** — `responses.ts`: `detail?: 'low' | 'high' | 'auto'`

Any spec-compliant client that doesn't explicitly send `detail` on every `input_image` part hits this. We hit it downstream in [ai-dynamo/dynamo#9470](https://github.com/ai-dynamo/dynamo/pull/9470) (had to shadow `EasyInputMessage` + `EasyInputContent` + `InputImageContent` as a workaround); the error was non-obvious to debug because the untagged-enum wrap-up hides the actual missing-field cause.

## Root cause

`InputImageContent.detail` lacks `#[serde(default)]`. `ImageDetail` already derives `Default` with `#[default] Auto`, so the fix is a one-attribute change.

## Proposed fix

```diff
 pub struct InputImageContent {
     /// The detail level of the image to be sent to the model. One of \`high\`, \`low\`, or \`auto\`.
-    /// Defaults to \`auto\`.
+    /// Defaults to \`auto\` when omitted in JSON input.
+    #[serde(default)]
     pub detail: ImageDetail,
```

Mirrors the precedent set by #527 which fixed the same class of bug on `EasyInputMessage.r#type` and `WebSearchApproximateLocation.r#type`.

I have a PR ready with this fix + two focused integration tests appended to `tests/responses_input_item_serde.rs` (one for the `EasyMessage` path, one for the strict `Item::Message(Input::User)` path). All existing tests + new tests pass; `cargo fmt --check` and `cargo clippy -D warnings` clean.

End-to-end reproducer (released v0.38.1 fails with the exact error above; patched build succeeds with `detail` defaulted) available on request.
